ames © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from East and West Hartford (Northumberland), Hartforth in Gilling (North Yorkshire), Hartford (Cheshire), or Hertford (Hertfordshire); less probably from Hartford End in Felsted (Essex) or Hartfordbridge in Elvetham (Hampshire). The placenames derive from Old English <i>heorot</i> ‘hart, stag’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah Ann Hartford was born in 1390, in Essex, England, United Kingdom. She married John Harris. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1450, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1390–1450":"1390–1450","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1425–1452":"1425–1452","1425–1480":"1425–1480","1425":"1425","1400":"1400","1452":"1452","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1664141, Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Prittlewell, Essex, England":"Prittlewell, Essex, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Syle